This paper is about machine reading comprehension (MRC), which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a methodology for evaluating MRC datasets, which involves machine learning and data analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the design of MRC datasets, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
